{"id": "EUVD-2004-2527", "enisaUuid": "95f4c51c-cbac-3916-9f71-ce08dfc4593b", "description": "The exit_thread function (process.c) in Linux kernel 2.6 through 2.6.5 does not invalidate the per-TSS io_bitmap pointers if a process obtains IO access permissions from the ioperm function but does not drop those permissions when it exits, which allows other processes to access the per-TSS pointers, access restricted memory locations, and possibly gain privileges.", "datePublished": "2005-10-25T04:00:00", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-08T01:29:13", "baseScore": 7.5, "baseScoreVersion": "2.0", "baseScoreVector": "AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P", "references": ["http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v2.6/ChangeLog-2.6.6", "https://exchange.xforce.ibmcloud.com/vulnerabilities/16106", "http://www.osvdb.org/5997", "http://www.securityfocus.com/bid/10302", "http://www.ussg.iu.edu/hypermail/linux/kernel/0405.0/1242.html", "http://secunia.com/advisories/11577", "http://www.ussg.iu.edu/hypermail/linux/kernel/0405.0/1265.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2004-2536"], "assigner": "mitre", "epss": 0.48, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "6f0bc703-7fe8-3bfc-b066-738026ab20d4", "product": {"name": "n/a"}, "product_version": "n/a"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "ccc24cd0-d93c-3222-aa14-c0f84bbeee08", "vendor": {"name": "n/a"}}], "isExploited": false}